        You can view the Enterprise Design System (FDS) <eds-link eds-new-window eds-href="https://design.xyz.com/fds/web/data-entry/radio/#visual-design-specifications">design guidance</eds-link> for this component.
    </section>
    
    {% filter markdown %}
    ## Use when
    - A person may need to select a single option from a set of choices.
    - All of the options available need to be seen so they can be easily compared.

    ## Don't use when
    - There is a single binary choice to be made. Instead, use a <eds-link eds-href="/components/checkbox/checkbox.html">Checkbox</eds-link>.
    - There are more than 5–7 options. Instead, use a  <eds-link eds-href="/components/select/select.html">Select</eds-link>.
    - The options are easily predictable like a month or a state name. Instead, use a <eds-link eds-href="/components/select/select.html">Select</eds-link>.
    - More than one choice may be. Instead, use a <eds-link eds-href="/components/checkbox/checkbox.html">Checkbox</eds-link>.

    ## Behavior
    - The actual size of "small", "medium", and "large" Radio Buttons will change in response to browser width.
    - The touch target includes the control and the <eds-link eds-href="/components/label/label.html">Label</eds-link>.
    - Only set a default choice when it makes sense from the perspective of someone making a selection.
    - Include an item labeled "None" when there's an option to not select one of the items otherwise displayed.
    - Selection data is submitted using a <eds-link eds-href="/components/button/button.html">Button</eds-link>.

    ## Content
    - Write the Radio Button text and <eds-link eds-href="/components/microcopy/microcopy.html">Microcopy</eds-link> clearly and concisely.
    - Always use sentence case.
